    "en": "Idoneal numbers completeness conjecture",
    "ja": null,
    "latex": "Equivalent definition: A positive integer $n$ is idoneal if and only if it cannot be written as\n$ab + bc + ac$ for distinct positive integers $a, b,$ and $c$.\n-/\ndef IsIdoneal (n : ℕ) : Prop :=\n  0 < n ∧\n    ¬ ∃ a b c : ℕ,\n      0 < a ∧ a < b ∧ b < c ∧ n = a * b + b * c + a * c\n\n/--\nThe 65 known idoneal numbers that are conjectured to be the only idoneal numbers.\n-/\ndef knownIdonealNumbers : Finse",
